HEADWORD: Deutoxide
<hw>Deu*tox"ide</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>deut-</ets> + <ets>oxide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
compound containing in the molecule two atoms of oxygen united with some
other element or radical; -- usually called <altname>dioxide</altname>,
or less frequently, <altname>binoxide</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

